label chapter12:

    # [Scene: Kelp Farm Platform | Dusk]

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Metal groaning, a thousand wet slaps as kelp hits timber, muffled shouts, the distant engine of a press drone]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: String ostinato, staccato—urgent]
    "You are knee‑deep in brine and broken promise. The salt is in your hair and in the scrape along your palm where a cable snagged; it tastes like the inside of an old wound. Around you,"
    "people move like a net under tension—some steady hands and faces you know, some pressed with a new, raw fear."
    "You grip the brass compass at your throat because it is the only unbroken circle you have left. It cools your skin, steadies your breath, and does not answer the question battering against your ribs: was this courage or ruin?"
    show kai_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    kai_navarro "We can spool the lines around the pilings and—if we run the aft tether, the module will pivot into the lee—"
    "You cut across him because there are too many hands and not enough time."
    show mara_linh_alvarez at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_linh_alvarez "Not with that tear in the coupling. If it goes, it’ll take the next line with it. Pull the left flank in—slow, not in bursts. Dr. Leila, get a thermal on the buoyancy tanks; we need to know which are compromised."
    show dr_leila_osei at center:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_leila_osei "On it. If the bladder's punctured, we lose lift. I can rig a temporary chamber but I need time and a dry seal."
    "Her voice is a scalpel. You want to bark, to tell everyone to stop and listen, but the sea keeps speaking in sudden hits—the sound of wood shearing, the sure caw of a gull deciding whether to loot a floating panel."
    "A volunteer stumbles, bringing up a thin line of blood. Juno is there a heartbeat later, grabbing your sleeve with fingers that smell like fried dough and fear."
    hide kai_navarro
    show juno_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    juno_alvarez "Sis—there's a kid under the platform! He won't stop crying."
    "You taste the whole Atlantic in your mouth. The choice you made—whichever form of action you took—has become immediate and physical: injured bodies, a half-ruined reef, cameras already clicking in the distance. Rescue is now triage;"
    "persuasion is now hauling, and the town's hope is threaded through pulleys and wet hands."
    "Nita arrives, hands already raw, voice low but iron-strong."
    hide mara_linh_alvarez
    show anita_nita_ramirez at right:
        zoom 0.7

    anita_nita_ramirez "We hold this piece, Mara. We don't let it go. We patch what we can, move what we can't. The kids are safe on the raised board—Sol has them—"
    "You can feel the town's heartbeat in her words. Dr. Leila returns, breathless and holding a sensor."

    dr_leila_osei "Two compromised bladders. One module is adrift—it's heading for the brackish channel. If it breaks surface near the shipping lane, Blackbrand will spin it into a headline overnight. We need salvage now."
    "Kai Navarro's hands hover on your shoulder. For a second he is steady—you can feel his warmth—but then his jaw tightens."
    hide dr_leila_osei
    show kai_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    kai_navarro "We can chase it. We have boats. I'll lead—I'll—"
    "You stop him with a look, sharper than your words."
    hide juno_alvarez
    show mara_linh_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_linh_alvarez "No. Not a chase that risks people. We rig a containment net at the mouth of the channel and tow slow. Leila—list the tools and men. Nita, get me lines. Juno stay with the child—keep him talking."
    "There is no time to breathe. You organize with the muscle memory of someone who has done the hard, unglamorous work of saving things before. But organization is not immunity to consequence."

    menu:
        "Shout orders, push urgency":
            "You raise your voice, the command slicing through panic. People snap into roles with immediate, brutal efficiency; a volunteer snaps a knot wrong and curses, but the net slides into place faster."
        "Bend to the smallest person, calm":
            "You crouch to the child, put salt-wet hair from his forehead, and ask his name. His sobs slow. Around you, hands find tasks gentler; a steady rhythm replaces the first wild panic."

    # --- merge ---
    "You choose both without thinking: the voice that commands and the hand that soothes. It is what you have always been in Marisport—both anchor and flint."
    # [/INTERACTION]
    hide anita_nita_ramirez
    hide kai_navarro
    hide mara_linh_alvarez

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The hiss of a rope under load, a child's sniffling, the flat thump of a crate belly against a piling]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Percussive, rising; brass wails like a distant foghorn]
    "The module drifts farther, hits the current, and then a winch takes the strain. For a breath you think you will wrench it back to safety."
    "Then the winch gives with a sound like a snapped jaw. The module spins free, slides under a piling, and is gone—rattled wood, trailing kelp like a severed braid."
    "An audible, collective intake—then a quiet that is all teeth. Someone swears. Kai's shoulders fold for half a beat as if the ocean's weight has found him."
    show kai_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    kai_navarro "We should have anchored farther out. I—"
    show mara_linh_alvarez at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_linh_alvarez "We did what we could with what we had. Don't start the blame clock now."
    "He looks at you like you have slapped him. There's grief there that tastes like accusation and apology both. He presses his palms flat to his face, then looks away."
    # [Scene: Brackish Channel | Night]
    hide kai_navarro
    hide mara_linh_alvarez

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Drone hum, muffled radios, the crackle of a law-enforcement channel]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, relentless drums; violin dissonance]
    "The channel where the module disappeared is dark and hungry. A Blackbrand security launch idles at the edge, its corporate crest a bright, clinical ring against mud and water. There are men with clipboards and a woman in a tailored waterproof coat—a PR liaison, efficient as a scalpel."
    "You know enough about corporate playbooks to recognize the posture: they are already staging a narrative. Two of their men snap pictures with devices; the PR woman angles for a line that will make them look"
    "calm, responsible. Behind her, a municipal inspector with a flashlight and a thin smile you've seen at hearings checks his notes."

    "Blackbrand Rep" "We can offer—"
    "You want to spit. You want to say that the 'offer' has skinned half the town and that middling assurances don't fix torn kelp beds. But you are a leader in a room that people look to for stead."
    show mara_linh_alvarez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_linh_alvarez "Right now, people are injured and a module is lost. We need cooperation to salvage and to assess damage. You have the cranes; we have the local knowledge. If you're serious, show it."
    "The PR woman tilts her head; her smile is a thin blade that doesn't hide the ledger in her eyes."

    "Blackbrand Rep" "We are committed to Marisport's safety. We'll provide support—after an assessment. Liability and procedure, you understand."

    mara_linh_alvarez "If you wait for an 'assessment' while the tide takes the reef? We will lose what we can no longer afford to lose."
    "The rep's smile doesn't change. A camera drone dips low and records your face. Someone near you hisses—'recorders'—and already threads of fear and fury knit together across the crowd. A man in a municipal vest clears his throat."

    "Municipal Inspector" "Legal counsel recommends documenting and—"

    mara_linh_alvarez "Then document. But don't use that as an excuse to sit idle while kelp and oysters are ripped out by the current."
    "The exchange is a high-wire act. The crowd's tone splits: some cheering your push, some whispering that this proves recklessness. An older fisherman mutters into his hood; a younger volunteer looks as if she wants to throw herself into the water."
    "A notification vibrates in Dr. Leila's pocket; she reads and her face drains."
    show dr_leila_osei at right:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_leila_osei "Funders. They're pulling their emergency disbursements—saying 'unacceptable risk.' There's an email from a counsel—possible liability inquiry."
    "The words are cold and precise. They arrive like a second accident."
    "Kai Navarro moves close, jaw working."
    show kai_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    kai_navarro "We have to show them something that works. Or we—mend. We—"
    "You feel a pressure building behind your eyes, the tightness that comes from being stretched. You think of your father's boat, the way it stayed afloat because someone had spent hours sewing its seams. You think"
    "of Juno's crooked laugh the week before and the photo in your pocket you haven't shown anyone."

    mara_linh_alvarez "We need data, Leila. Bring what you can to the promenade. Get video, samples. Nita—keep the market open; keep people fed. Kai—manage the volunteers. No more hero stunts. No more solo chases."
    "He nods. His eyes are so bright they hurt."

    kai_navarro "No more solo chases."

    menu:
        "Order the group to legal-first—document, protect, then act":
            "You call for a perimeter and for evidence collection; the volunteers grumble but fall into a different, exhausted rhythm. The PR drone circles, but the story becomes harder to diminish."
        "Push for immediate, visible action to reclaim narrative":
            "You shout for lights and cameras—drag a near-intact kelp mattress onto the platform, make a demonstration of what survives. People rally; Blackbrand's PR pauses—but the risk goes up and a volunteer twists an ankle."

    # --- merge ---
    "The night slips into something stranger: a theater where every movement will be recorded and used. You can feel the story of tonight being written by others who will not feel the cold under their nails."
    # [/INTERACTION]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A siren wails briefly as a corporate van settles by the promenade; a clacking of keyboards from someone already composing press statements]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Crescendo—tension threading into near-chaos]
    "Nita puts a hand on your forearm, grounding."
    hide mara_linh_alvarez
    show anita_nita_ramirez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    anita_nita_ramirez "We did the right thing. Even if they call it reckless, we tried to do the living work."
    "You want to believe her so badly, but the evidence is sharp: a broken module, a bruised volunteer, the smell of burnt electrical insulation. Somewhere in the city, a funder's email lands on a warm desk"
    "and the red line of a retraction is drawn. You picture grant money clicking away like tide through a sieve."
    # [Scene: Promenade | Late Night]
    hide dr_leila_osei
    hide kai_navarro
    hide anita_nita_ramirez

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_4 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Low murmurs, the scrape of a cart, far-off amplified corporate voices being drowned by a chant]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A mournful cello with jagged flourishes]
    "You walk the promenade at the end of the night like someone going through the rooms of a house that has lost its heat. The living reef you imagined—kelp beds, baby oysters—are a half-salvaged memory: some"
    "fronds cling to anchored ropes; a few clusters of oysters grit on a rock. The rest is a litter of foam and broken panels."
    "An envelope waits at the community table: a terse legal notice from an insurer; another: a well-meaning—but cold—press release from town hall suggesting an investigation into 'community-led interventions.' Cameras line the far side with expressions that want to know exactly who to blame."
    "Kai Navarro catches up to you, boots heavy with water. He had been at the brim of collapse all night; now he steadies, then collapses beside you on a wet bench."
    show kai_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    kai_navarro "They called us dangerous. They called us 'amateurs.' They—' He stops, swallows, and his hands shake. 'Mara, I'm sorry. I—"
    "You turn to him, and for an instant there is everything—the warmth you have clung to, the small, private kindnesses, the nights of shared tea. Then the rawness of what just happened—the loss of public trust, the wounded bodies, the looming lawsuits—crushes the tenderness down like a crashing wave."
    show mara_linh_alvarez at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_linh_alvarez "Sorry doesn't fix a reef. It doesn't pay to replace the modules or the grants that vanished. It doesn't undo the broken ankle. Sorry—' Your voice curdles into a laugh that tastes like rust. 'Sorry is a small boat on a hard sea."
    "Kai flinches, as if the laugh were a slap. He reaches for you and you do not step into his arms."

    kai_navarro "Then don't carry it alone. Let me—let me take some of this, Mara."

    mara_linh_alvarez "You keep saying that. But every time we've reached, something else breaks. I don't know if we have the margin to keep being brave the way we were tonight."
    "He looks at you like someone seeing a map of a place they've always loved, now scribbled with warnings."

    kai_navarro "I'm not asking to be your shield. I— I want to be the one who steadies the ropes. If you want me to step back, tell me. If you want me to step up, tell me that too."
    "You think of every compromise that cost a neighbor's home, the deals struck behind doors with glossy brochures and handshakes. You think of the look on Evelyn Black's face—the unreadable set of someone who has decided sacrifice is acceptable because it's tidy—and your throat tightens."

    mara_linh_alvarez "I don't know, Kai. I don't know how much more we can afford to gamble on 'we' when 'we' looks different to so many. The town is split. Funders are gone. Blackbrand will paint tonight as proof we needed them."

    "A vehicle with corporate lighting idles across the water, its logo glowing like a promise you've learned to mistrust. A press vehicle's mirror flashes; someone intones a line for the cameras" "Well‑intentioned, but reckless."
    "Juno arrives silently and drops a bag of harvested seedlings at your feet—mangled but alive."
    show juno_alvarez at center:
        zoom 0.7

    juno_alvarez "Some made it. I thought you should see."
    "You look at the green, at the thin stubborn life clinging to mud and rope. It is almost obscene how small it seems against the scale of loss—yet it is also proof that not everything went under."
    "Nita squeezes your hand, fierce and simple."
    hide kai_navarro
    show anita_nita_ramirez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    anita_nita_ramirez "You did this for the right reasons, Mara. People will remember."
    "You wish that memory could pay rent, fund oyster leases, and buy back the trust frayed tonight."
    "The night ends not with a single resolution but with a stack of consequences. Blackbrand's PR begins to reframe the story online—'risky community maneuver'—and a legal notice arrives in the morning. Funders fade like retreating tide."
    "The town divides: some call for hearings and formal oversight, others rally in the market, fingers raw from rope."
    "In the center of it all, you stand, raw and alone in a way that stings because Kai did not step into the space you had imagined he'd fill—he tried, but the chasm is not only physical; it's now threaded with insurance forms and public narratives you cannot control."
    "You pull the brass compass from beneath your shirt. It is warm from your skin, its scuff dull and honest. You close your fingers around it like a vow and, for the first time in a long while, let something break open—not into action or plan, but into grief."

    mara_linh_alvarez "I thought leadership meant knowing the hard things and shouldering them with certainty. Tonight I learned it's also knowing the damage you can cause even when your heart is in the right place. The sea does not care for intentions."
    hide mara_linh_alvarez
    hide juno_alvarez
    hide anita_nita_ramirez

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_5 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A single gull cries; footsteps recede; a small child laughs faintly in the distance]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fading, a single low cello note that does not resolve]
    "You do not have easy answers. You have a reef that survived enough to be a symbol of stubborn life and a broken module that will be tomorrow's headline. You have volunteers who will need months"
    "of rebuilding, an injured neighbor who will need care, and a city hall that will ask for hearings where nuance is a poor currency."
    "Kai stands and hesitates at the edge of your orbit, wanting to help but already wearing the weight of the criticism like wet clothes. He doesn't know if his presence comforts or burdens you now."
    show kai_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    kai_navarro "Whatever you do next—I'll be on the front steps, not the headlines. If you want me there."
    "You close the compass in your hand as if closing a book."
    show mara_linh_alvarez at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mara_linh_alvarez "Then come stand where we'll be building—not under the lights. Build with us, not for the story they'll tell."
    "He nods, and the nod is small and brave and fragile."
    "You turn away from the promenade lights and look out where the last of the kelp fronds move with the night tide. For all the loss and for all the blame to come, a sliver survived."
    "It will take time, and money, and more people who will not want this life—who may leave. But the sliver is enough to be proof that what you tried had teeth to it."
    "You breathe in and let the briny air fill you. It tastes like the end of something and the seed of what might yet be. You think of Juno, of Nita's hands, of Dr. Leila's data"
    "clutched tight like a talisman. You think of the children—of how the next morning will be full of whispered rumors and the long haul of repair."
    "You do not promise triumph. You do not promise reconciliation. You make a quieter vow: you will stay. Not because you are certain of success, but because leaving would be the last, bitter way to let the sea and the suits decide what remains."
    hide kai_navarro
    hide mara_linh_alvarez

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_6 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The tide moves; distant machinery hums like a city heart; a single, steady breath]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single, unresolved chord]

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_7 at full_bg
    "THE END"
